      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable that it feels rigged; sometimes the financial jargon is designed to be confusing, which is a tactic some loan servicers use. You should watch out for fees like late payment penalties, origination fees, and any compounding frequency that might be more aggressive than you expect. Also, if you have variable interest rates, the rate itself can change, which will directly impact how much interest is charged each month. Keeping a close eye on those variable rate changes is crucial.",
